-- European Banks Sell Bonds to Get Ahead of Stress Test Results, FT Reports
-- Alan Purkiss
-- 2010-07-12T05:06:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/european-banks-sell-bonds-to-get-ahead-of-stress-tests-ft-says.html

          
          
             European banks are getting ahead of
stress tests by securing funds in bond markets, the Financial
Times reported.  
 Last week, 18.3 billion euros ($23.2 billion) of bonds were
sold by banks, up from 4.8 billion euros the previous week, the
newspaper said, citing Dealogic.  
 Barclays Plc, BNP Paribas SA, HSBC Holdings Plc and UBS AG
are among banks that went to the market to obtain long-term
funds, the FT said.  
